    Proper nouns.
    As we have already seen&#8212;(46), repeated below as (55)--a definite description that looks like a proper noun (the petite, 29-year-old Ms. Johnson) may in fact be anaphoric.
    This is not always a problem, as the system does attempt to find antecedents for these definites, as well, but if the antecedent is not found (as in the example below) the description is incorrectly classified as discourse-new.
    The petite, 29-year-old Ms. Johnson .
